wspan=\"1\"><p>Warranty</p></td><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>12-year warranty extendable 25 years</p></td></tr></tbody></table>',99.00,NULL,'/uploads/datasheets/1761603892320-jkzmm47jpo.pdf','a0b3eb1a-4e72-11f0-bbc5-06479488ad4b','Q.PEAK DUO BLK ML-G9+',0.00,'[{\"type\":\"fixed\",\"name\":\"Standard Shipping\",\"description\":\"3-5 business days\",\"cost\":50},{\"type\":\"local_pickup\",\"name\":\"Local Pickup\",\"description\":\"Pick up from our location\",\"warehouse_ids\":[\"main-warehouse-id\"]}]',0,'calculated',0.00,'q-cells-380-watt-solar-panel-qpeak-duo-blk-ml-g9',1,'2025-10-27 22:24:53','2025-10-27 22:27:27'),('c67af604-9104-11f0-95d2-0637a5b9918d','Square D Stainless Steel General Duty 60A 240V Fusible Safety Switch','<h1 style=\"text-align: left\">Square D 60 Amp 120/240 VAC Fusible Safety Switch</h1><p style=\"text-align: left\">Poles: 2<br>Manufacturer Part Number: D222NRB</p><p style=\"text-align: left\">Switches are rainproof NEMA 3R with external lockable switch handle and door. Switches serve as service disconnects (non-fusible) and overcurrent devices (fusible) for 120/240 Vac systems. Only the fusible switches include a factory installed neutral assembly. Switches include main lugs and ground screw. 3R switches accept top bolt-on hubs.</p><p style=\"text-align: left\"><em>For Square D safety switches, the \"N\" in NRB stands for Neutral.<br>NRB = Isolated terminal block equipped switch. For Square D RB models = No terminal block.</em></p>',95.00,NULL,NULL,'b5ef143e-4e72-11f0-bbc5-06479488ad4b','D222NRB',0.00,'[{\"type\":\"local_pickup\",\"name\":\"Local Pickup\",\"description\":\"Pick up from our location\",\"warehouse_ids\":[\"main-warehouse-id\"]},{\"type\":\"free\",\"name\":\"Standard Shipping\",\"description\":\"3-5 business days\"}]',0,'calculated',0.00,'square-d-stainless-steel-general-duty-60a-240v-fusible-safety-switch-d222nrb',1,'2025-09-14 00:50:14','2025-09-14 00:59:30'),('c6b303ea-4eb5-11f0-bbc5-06479488ad4b','Tigo 3.8 kWh Inverter','<p>Tigo TSI-3.8K-US 3.8kW Energy Storage Hybrid Inverter</p>',400.00,NULL,NULL,'b5ef143e-4e72-11f0-bbc5-06479488ad4b','TSI-3.8K-US',0.00,'[]',0,'calculated',0.00,'tigo-38-kwh-inverter-tsi-38k-us',0,'2025-06-21 15:38:27','2025-10-03 05:04:52'),('c877a8fc-c215-11f0-9ad4-0637a5b9918d','EZ Solar JB-1.2 Rooftop PV Junction Box','<p>EZ Solar Rooftop PV Junction Box - Asphalt Shingle - Made from advanced durable polycarbonate. EZ Solar believes innovations is key to making Solar Simple! The most revolutionary junction bos on the market just got better! Designed with the installer in mind, the JB-1.2 makes installation fast and easy.</p><h4>Simple to install</h4><ul><li><p>Minimal Shingle Cutting</p></li><li><p>Enter Through 3 Sidewalls</p></li><li><p>Wider and Taller Sidewalls</p></li></ul><h4>High Quality</h4><ul><li><p>Made from advanced durable poly-carbonate + superior components, UL1741, Type 3R</p></li><li><p>3 patented layers of water protection</p></li><li><p>2 Weep Holes for breath-ability</p></li></ul><h3>Specifications:</h3><ul><li><p>Maximum Voltage: 1,000 Volts</p></li><li><p>Maximum Current: 80 Amps</p></li><li><p>Allowable Wire: 14 AWG – 6 AWG</p></li><li><p>Spacing: Please maintain a spacing of at least ½” between uninsulated live parts and fittings for conduit, armored cable, and uninsulated live parts of opposite polarity.</p></li><li><p>Enclosure Rating: Type 3R</p></li><li><p>Roof Slope Range: 2.5 – 12:12</p></li><li><p>Max Side Wall Fitting Size: 1”</p></li><li><p>Max Floor Pass-Through Fitting Size: 1”</p></li><li><p>Ambient Operating Conditions: (-35°C) - (+75°C)</p></li></ul>',50.00,NULL,'/uploads/datasheets/1763205913380-n3ze9w7gajl.pdf','be84ed54-4e72-11f0-bbc5-06479488ad4b','JB-1.2',0.00,'[]',0,'calculated',0.00,'ez-solar-jb-12-rooftop-pv-junction-box-jb-12',1,'2025-11-15 11:25:26','2025-11-15 11:25:26'),('cd6f2a94-c364-11f0-9ad4-0637a5b9918d','Pallet Of 23 Sunpower 390 Watt Solar Panels','<p>This is a pallet of 23 SunPower 390 W solar panels.  It ships for free anywhere in the US (except Alaska and Hawaii).  </p><p>The SunPower Performance Series 390W monocrystalline solar panel is designed for commercial use. It is built to be highly durable, resistant to harsh conditions like salt, acid, and ammonia, and can withstand significant mechanical loads. The \"COM\" in the SKU indicates its suitability for commercial-scale installations.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Technical specifications</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Power Output:</strong> 390 Watts</p></li><li><p><strong>Cells:</strong> 120 monocrystalline PERC cells</p></li><li><p><strong>Dimensions:</strong> Approximately 81.4 inches x 39.3 inches x 1.81 inches</p></li><li><p><strong>Weight:</strong> Approximately 50.9 pounds (23.1 kg)</p></li><li><p><strong>Frame:</strong> 1.81\" thick anodized aluminum alloy</p></li><li><p><strong>Durability:</strong> Certified for environmental resistance, including salt, acid, and ammonia, and can handle mechanical loads up to 5400 Pa (front) and 2400 Pa (back)&nbsp;</p></li></ul><p><strong>Key features</strong></p><ul><li><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" class=\"text-blue-600 underline GI370e\" href=\"https://www.google.com/search?q=Maxeon+cell+technology&amp;rlz=1C5GCEM_enUS1118US1118&amp;oq=SKU%3A+SPR-P19-390-COM&amp;gs_lcrp=EgZjaHJvbWUyBggAEEUYOTIGCAEQRRg60gEHMTc2ajBqN6gCALACAA&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;mstk=AUtExfC_8gSuunZDw-OtyhsgrhzpAsloxi9ATvrS7VC3QrfonQKe4Y6O1lF_TZ5JKHRYG7eJa7oNjrCrd_-L_tJcuXY7iqUPcEnGTGzy_JZ8p7IlV_bhkEz1rodFHYuIgshke7iPKOK1pfMyTJDBE3pCME-GU182pkXOj4vmVwVB6FP8dig&amp;csui=3&amp;ved=2ahUKEwi74MGHnumQAxWuIUQIHbTzMtIQgK4QegQIBhAB\"><strong>Maxeon cell technology</strong></a><strong>:</strong> This technology is used in SunPower Performance panels to increase efficiency and improve performance in shaded conditions.</p></li><li><p><strong>High Reliability:</strong> The panels are built for longevity and backed by a 25-year product and performance warranty.</p></li><li><p><strong>Commercial Application:</strong> The \"COM\" designation signifies that this panel is suitable for large-scale commercial rooftop installations.&nbsp;</p></li></ul><table class=\"table-auto border-collapse border border-gray-300\" style=\"min-width: 50px\"><colgroup><col style=\"min-width: 25px\"><col style=\"min-width: 25px\"></colgroup><tbody><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Length</p></td><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>81.4in</p></td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Width</p></td><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>39.3in</p></td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Rated Power Output</p></td><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>390 W</p></td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Voltage (VOC)</p></td><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>52.3V</p></td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Maximum String Voltage</p></td><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>1000V</p></td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Number of cells</p></td><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>120</p></td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Cell Type</p></td><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Monocrystalline</p></td></tr><tr class=\"\"><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>Rated Efficiency</p></td><td class=\"border border-gray-300 p-2\" colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\"><p>18.9%</p